def show_results(D,title):
    # D is a dictionary with classical bits as keys and count as value
    # example: D = {'000': 497, '001': 527}
    data = [x / 1024 for x in list(D.values())]
    plt.bar(range(len(D)), data, align='center')
    plt.xticks(range(len(D)), list(D.keys()))
    plt.ylabel('Probability')
    plt.xlabel('State')
    plt.title(title)
    plt.show()

# Execute circuit, display a histogram of the results
def execute_locally(qc, draw_circuit=False):
    # Compile and run the Quantum circuit on a simulator backend
    backend_sim = Aer.get_backend('qasm_simulator')
    job_sim = execute(qc, backend_sim)
    result_sim = job_sim.result()
    result_counts = result_sim.get_counts(qc)
    
    # Print the results
    
    return result_counts

Estratégias¶

$$\newcommand{\ket}[1]{\left|{#1}\right\rangle}$$$$\newcommand{\bra}[1]{\left\langle{#1}\right|}$$$$C = \begin{bmatrix} 1 & 0 \\ 0 & 1 \end{bmatrix} =U(0,0,0)$$$$E = \begin{bmatrix} 1 & 0 \\ 0 & 1 \end{bmatrix} = U(\pi,\pi,\pi)$$$$A = \begin{bmatrix} i & 0 \\ 0 & -i \end{bmatrix} = U(0,-\frac{\pi}{2},-\frac{\pi}{2})$$
In [38]:
C = (0,0,0)
E = (pi,pi,pi)
A = (0,-pi/2,-pi/2)
options = [C,E,A]
iten = [[i,j,k,l] for i in range(3)  for j in range(3) for k in range(3) for l in range(3)] #cria array de permutacoes de estrategias
itec = [[i,j,k,l] for i in ['C','E','A']  for j in ['C','E','A'] for k in ['C','E','A'] for l in ['C','E','A']] #equivalente apenas com caracteres

def create_circuit(strategy):

    qc = QuantumCircuit(4)
    
    #J
    qc.cx(0,1)
    qc.cx(0,2)
    qc.cx(0,3)
    qc.u(np.pi/2,np.pi/2,-np.pi/2,0)
    qc.cz(0,1)
    qc.cz(0,2)
    qc.cz(0,3)
    qc.cx(0,1)
    qc.cx(0,2)
    qc.cx(0,3)

    qc.barrier()
    #Estrategias dos jogadores (dependendo da estrategia aplica gate u com os angulos especificos à escolha do jogador)
    a = options[strategy[3]]
    b = options[strategy[2]]
    c = options[strategy[1]]
    d = options[strategy[0]]
    
    qc.u(*a,0)
    qc.u(*b,1)
    qc.u(*c,2)
    qc.u(*d,3)

    qc.barrier()
    
    
    #J dagger
    qc.cx(0,3)
    qc.cx(0,2)
    qc.cx(0,1)
    qc.cz(0,3)
    qc.cz(0,2)
    qc.cz(0,1)
    qc.u(-pi/2,+pi/2,-pi/2,0)
    qc.cx(0,3)
    qc.cx(0,2)
    qc.cx(0,1)


    #Measure qubits
    qc.measure_all()
    
    return qc

table = {}
table2 = {}
for i,it,itaux in zip(results,itec,iten):
    x = list(i.keys())[0][::-1]
    mx = '|'+str(x)+'>'
    
    if x == '0000':
        pAlice,pBob,pColin,pDoug = 6,6,6,6
    if x == '0001':
        pAlice,pBob,pColin,pDoug = 4,4,4,8
    if x == '0010':
        pAlice,pBob,pColin,pDoug = 4,4,8,4
    if x == '0011':
        pAlice,pBob,pColin,pDoug = 3,3,4,4
    if x == '0100':
        pAlice,pBob,pColin,pDoug = 4,8,4,4
    if x == '0101':
        pAlice,pBob,pColin,pDoug = 3,4,3,4
    if x == '0110':
        pAlice,pBob,pColin,pDoug = 3,4,4,3
    if x == '0111':
        pAlice,pBob,pColin,pDoug = 0,3,3,3
    if x == '1000':
        pAlice,pBob,pColin,pDoug = 8,4,4,4
    if x == '1001':
        pAlice,pBob,pColin,pDoug = 4,3,3,4
    if x == '1010':
        pAlice,pBob,pColin,pDoug = 4,3,4,3
    if x == '1011':
        pAlice,pBob,pColin,pDoug = 3,0,3,3
    if x == '1100':
        pAlice,pBob,pColin,pDoug = 4,4,3,3
    if x == '1101':
        pAlice,pBob,pColin,pDoug = 3,3,0,3
    if x == '1110':
        pAlice,pBob,pColin,pDoug = 3,3,3,0
    if x == '1111':
        pAlice,pBob,pColin,pDoug = 1,1,1,1
        
    table[u'\u2297'.join(it)] = [mx,pAlice,pBob,pColin,pDoug]
    table2[''.join([str(x) for x in itaux])] = [mx,pAlice,pBob,pColin,pDoug]
df = pd.DataFrame(table,index = ["End State", "Payoff Alice", "Payoff Bob", "Payoff Colin" ,"Payoff Doug"]).T
